'''Alessandro Palma di Cesnola''' (1839–1914) was an archaeologist who excavated in [[Cyprus]]. He worked at [[Paphos]], where he was U.S. vice-consul, and [[Salamis, Cyprus|Salamis]] on behalf of the British government. The results of these are described in ''Salaminia'' (1882).<ref name="EB1911">{{EB1911|inline=y|wstitle=Cesnola, Luigi Palma di|volume=5|page=768}}</ref>

Alessandro was the brother of the better known archaeologist [[Luigi Palma Di Cesnola]].

